[Student "E"]
{[show NESW]

[showcards W:DJ]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown, (wild).

Partner led the \DJ; \DQ from dummy, \DK from you and ruffed by South.

South then pulls two rounds of trumps, (West discards on the second one), followed by his \SQ, dummy's \S A K and dummy's \DA. South discards \Cs on the last two cards.

The \C6 is then played from dummy and you must make a decision - \CA or \C2?

When you have made your choice click NEXT. [choose-card C2] [NEXT]

[clear-commentary]

Play the \C2.

You have a full count on South's hand. He started with 2 \Ss, 7 \Hs, and no \Ds. His other 4 cards must have been \Cs, and he has discarded 2 of them.

So he has 2 \Cs left in his hand. If one of them is the \CK and you play your \CA then you have handed him the contract.

By playing low you give him a guess to make. If he plays the \CK he will make the contract, but if he plays the \CJ he will go down. He will probably play the \CJ, figuring you woudn't have the nerve to duck with the \CA. He'll know better next time he plays against you.}
[Play "W"]DJ

