{[show NE]

[showcards S:SA,C2 W:SK]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown.

West led the \SK, won by South's \SA. South played a small \C to dummy's \CA, then led dummy's \HJ.

What do you play? \HQ or \H4? 

When you have made your choice click NEXT. [choose-card H4] [NEXT]

[show NESW]

[clear-commentary]

Play the \H4.

Remember that South opened 1\H, so he has 5 of them. With only 3 trumps out he has no intention of finessing. Perhaps he led the \HJ just to tempt you to cover in this situation.

If you play low he will win with one of his high \Hs and then you will have a sure \H winner. Along with the \S winner West has you will defeat the slam.

If you cover the \HJ with your \HQ South will again win with one of his high ones. But now the position will be clear to South and he will return to dummy and play another \H, finessing your \H10. With no trump loser he will make the slam. }
[Play "W"]SK

