[showcards W:DJ]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \DJ and dummy's \DA wins the first trick. Declarer pulls trumps with dummy's \SK, then his \SA. He then plays his \DK and follows with \CQ, \CK and \CA, discarding a \H from his hand on the last.

With all that completed South plays the \HA. What do you play?

When you have made your choice click NEXT. [choose-card HK] [NEXT]

[clear-commentary]

Play the \HK.

It may look foolish to waste your \HK but look what will happen if you don't. South will follow up with another \H and when you win the \HK you will be forced to play a minor suit. Since both North and South are out of \Ds and \Cs you will be giving them a ruff-sluff and the contract.

But if you dump your \HK under South's \HA look at what's left. South has \H losers and when he plays a \H from either hand East will scoop up two tricks with his \H Q 10.}
[Play "W"]DJ

